Pupils have just a week to catch up before matric exams begin. JOHANNESBURG - Three months - that's how much schooling matrics at Eldorado Park Secondary School have lost this year. Teachers union Sadtu has been in a dispute with the school governing body over alleged unfair treatment. Now pupils have just a week to catch up before matric exams begin. READ: Eldorado Park community demands removal of teachers from school A learning camp has been set up by the Gauteng Education Department to help them. A vigorous seven-day programme has been put in place as they head to their matric exams. The matrics are relieved that they can finally receive some schooling. Sadtu is calling for an urgent intervention to resolve the impasse at the school.